(3, 2, 'training', '', 'Apple CEO Tim Cook advocates for inclusion and diversity. He has been instrumental in the company\'s initiatives to advance fairness and equality inside its ranks and across the technology sector.\r\n\r\nCook has prioritized diversity and inclusion at Apple because he believes it is proper and necessary for innovation and business success.\r\n\r\nUnconscious bias training, diverse recruitment, and employee resource groups contributed to his success.', '2024-05-02'),
(4, 2, 'women', '', 'Sheryl Sandberg\'s 2021 talk, \"Lean In,\" encourages women to lean into their careers and leadership roles. She urges women to stand up for one another and themselves to overcome societal and cultural hurdles.\r\n\r\nSandberg highlights the need to have distinct objectives and goals and be prepared to take calculated risks to achieve them.\r\n\r\nShe also underlines how crucial it is for more female leaders to advance diversity and gender equality across all industries.\r\n\r\nSandberg\'s speech also emphasizes collaboration. She urges women to mentor other women and look for sponsors and mentors themselves.\r\n\r\nThe \"Lean In\" talk by Sheryl Sandberg emphasizes women\'s voices and perspectives in all aspects of society.\r\n\r\nTo remove barriers and foster more inclusive and varied workplaces and communities, Sandberg urges women to pursue their professional ambitions with confidence and with the help of their communities.\r\n\r\n\"We need women at all levels, including the top, to change the dynamic, reshape the conversation, to make sure women\'s voices are heard and heeded, not overlooked and ignored.\"', '2024-05-02'),
(5, 3, '\"How to Live Before You Die\"', '', 'onsidering the YouTube video of Steve Jobs\' 2005 Stanford commencement speech has 24 million views, it\'s likely that you\'ve seen this one already.\r\n\r\nIn the speech, Jobs plays on two themes: connecting the dots (anecdote: how taking a calligraphy class helped inspire the design of the Mac) and love & loss (anecdote: how getting fired from Apple helped inspire his greatest innovations).\r\n\r\nPerhaps the most memorable part his speech comes at the end, when he quotes the (now-famous) lines from the final issue of his favorite publication, The Whole Earth Catalog:\r\n\r\n‚ÄúStay hungry. Stay foolish.‚Äù\r\n\r\nsteve jobs\r\n\r\n9. Matthew McConaughey: \"The Pursuit of Happiness\" (2022)\r\nTheme of the Speech: Discovering True Happiness and Fulfillment in Life.\r\n\r\nIn \"The Pursuit of Happiness,\" famed actor and motivational speaker Matthew McConaughey provides his enlightened viewpoint on obtaining true happiness and fulfillment.\r\n\r\nMcConaughey presents a genuine and approachable study of what it means to live a fulfilling life through sincere storytelling and personal anecdotes.\r\n\r\nThe speech discusses the significance of authenticity and remaining true to oneself. McConaughey encourages people to define their success rather than succumb to social press', '2024-05-11'),
(6, 3, '\"The Power of Self-Belief\" ', '', '-->Oprah Winfrey\'s 2020 speech \"The Power of Self-Belief\" emphasized the importance of self-assurance. She attributed her success to her unwavering self-assurance.\r\n\r\nAccording to Oprah, self-belief is not about being arrogant or overconfident. She stresses the significance of overcoming self-doubt and fear, which can prevent people from reaching their goals.\r\n\r\nOprah used personal stories to demonstrate how self-confidence has aided her in life and work. She encouraged her audience to believe in themselves and to embrace their inner strength.\r\n\r\nThe Power of Self-Belief\" reminded us how important it is to have faith in ourselves and our ability to succeed.', '2024-05-08'),
(23, 1, 'platform ttt', '', 'Before Barack Obama became the first African-American President of the United States, when he was little known outside the grassroots activist community in Chicago, he was given a national platform as the keynote speaker at the Democratic National Convention in 2004. He acknowledged what everyone was likely thinking and how surprising it was for him to be addressing the audience at the convention. But he started by stating his roots, which were not dissimilar from other Americans, who constitute, after all, a nation of immigrants. He infused the audience, nation and even the world with a sense of hope for the future. After this speech, he continued to connect with people and motivate them to elect him four years later to the highest office in the land.', '2024-05-03'),
(26, 0, 'h', '', 'mmm', '2024-05-29'),
(27, 0, 'cricketers ', '', 'ormer Australia cricketer Simon Katich has been the latest addition to bandwagon of experts and veteran cricketers to pick their preferred Team India squad for the impending T20 World Cup which will begin from June 1 onwards in the West Indies and the USA. Katich reveals his squad as Indian cricket fraternity wait with baited breath for the official announcement by BCCI\'s selection committee of the final 15 for the ICC tournament.', '2024-05-02'),
(28, 0, 'Cricket Tournament Cricket Tournament ', '', 'Cricket Tournament Cricket Tournament Cricket Tournament Cricket Tournament ', '2024-05-02'),
(31, 0, 'Complete diet plan for diabetics to lower ', '', 't is a common notion that food without onion and garlic does not taste good. If you feel the same way, you must try Dahi Aloo. This comforting salty, sour, and spicy dish is very easy to make and extremely comforting on your tummy and mouth. \r\n\r\nEasy Recipe For Dahi Aloo\r\nCheck out this easy no-onion and garlic recipe of dahi aloo to relish on lazy afternoons. \r\n\r\nFullscreen button\r\ndahi aloo recipe steps photo\r\ndahi aloo recipe steps photo\r\n¬© Provided by Her Zindagi\r\nImage courtesy: Facebook\r\n\r\nTake fresh potatoes, wash them thoroughly, peel them, and dice them. Make sure the size of each piece is medium, not too small nor too big. \r\nTransfer them to a pot with a high quantity of water and some salt to boil them until they are soft and edible. Then keep them aside.  \r\nTake a wok, and let it warm a little. Then pour the required amount of oil in it and let it heat for a while. \r\n\r\nExpand article logo  Continue reading\r\nOnce the oil is hot, prepare tempering by pouring a few mustard seeds and dried chilli, and let it cook until mustard seeds start to crackle. \r\nAfter that, add the required amount of curry leaves and let it fry for a bit.\r\nOnce done, add a pinch of hing (asafoetida). \r\nNext, add the boiled potatoes and mix them for some time.\r\nAfter that, you need to add some turmeric powder, coriander powder, and a very small amount of jeera (cumin) powder and garam masala. Cumin powder and garam masala are optional as the dominant flavour in the dish is the mustard seeds.\r\nNext add red chilli powder or green chillies, as per your choice. After adding salt as per your taste, give it a good mix while keeping it on medium flame. \r\nOnce the masala starts to get cooked and covers the potato pieces, add water as per your preferred consistency. \r\nWhile you leave it on the stove for cooking, pour some curd into a bowl and beat it until it is smoothened.\r\nOnce the gravy in the pan starts to bubble up, you will know that it is cooked.\r\nNext, lower the flame and add the beaten curd. Make sure to continuously stir it as otherwise it will curdle. \r\nOnce it starts to slightly bubble, turn the knob off. \r\nGarnish it with some fresh coriander and serve it hot with steaming soft phulke (bread).\r\n0\r\n', '2024-05-12'),
