(73, 11, 'Engineers...', '', ' Engineers‚Äô Day: In India, 15th September is recognized as Engineers‚Äô Day. Every year this day is celebrated on the birth anniversary of India‚Äôs greatest engineer Bharat Ratna Mokshagundam Visvesvaraya, who was born on 15th September 1861. He was awarded the highest civilian honor‚ÄîBharat Ratna in 1955 for numerous industrial, economical and social projects. M. Visvesvaraya is also known as the ‚ÄòDiwan of Mysore‚Äô. This day is celebrated in India to thank engineers for their contribution to society and applaud their dexterity and diligence. Engineers‚Äô Day: In India, 15th September is recognized as Engineers‚Äô Day. Every year this day is celebrated on the birth anniversary of India‚Äôs greatest engineer Bharat Ratna Mokshagundam Visvesvaraya, who was born on 15th September 1861. He was awarded the highest civilian honor‚ÄîBharat Ratna in 1955 for numerous industrial, economical and social projects. M. Visvesvaraya is also known as the ‚ÄòDiwan of Mysore‚Äô. This day is celebrated in India to thank engineers for their contribution to society and applaud their dexterity and diligence. Engineers‚Äô Day: In India, 15th September is recognized as Engineers‚Äô Day. Every year this day is celebrated on the birth anniversary of India‚Äôs greatest engineer Bharat Ratna Mokshagundam Visvesvaraya, who was born on 15th September 1861. He was awarded the highest civilian honor‚ÄîBharat Ratna in 1955 for numerous industrial, economical and social projects. M. Visvesvaraya is also known as the ‚ÄòDiwan of Mysore‚Äô. This day is celebrated in India to thank engineers for their contribution to society and applaud their dexterity and diligence. Engineers‚Äô Day: In India, 15th September is recognized as Engineers‚Äô Day. Every year this day is celebrated on the birth anniversary of India‚Äôs greatest engineer Bharat Ratna Mokshagundam Visvesvaraya, who was born on 15th September 1861. He was awarded the highest civilian honor‚ÄîBharat Ratna in